questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a low-latency financial transaction processor experiences high garbage collection pause times, culminating in `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Metaspace`. Analysis of the heap dump shows millions of dynamically generated classes. You locate the following Spring bean responsible for decorating outgoing payment tasks:

java
@Component
public class DynamicBillingService {
    public Object createMonitoredService(final Object target) {
        ProxyFactory factory = new ProxyFactory(target);
        factory.addAdvice(new PerformanceMonitorInterceptor());
        return factory.getProxy();
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot application experiences a slow, steady memory leak in the JVM Heap. APM tools indicate that the leak is associated with `ThreadLocal` variables used to store user session context. The system uses a customized `ThreadPoolTaskExecutor` for async processing:

java
@Configuration
public class AsyncConfig {
    @Bean(name = "asyncExecutor")
    public Executor asyncExecutor() {
        ThreadPoolTaskExecutor executor = new ThreadPoolTaskExecutor();
        executor.setCorePoolSize(10);
        executor.setMaxPoolSize(50);
        executor.initialize();
        return executor;
    }
}


The leak occurs despite the fact that a `ServletFilter` explicitly calls `UserContextHolder.clear()` inside a `finally` block for every incoming HTTP request.
